# Frontend UI & styling

## Component library

- Use **Ant Design (antd)** components by default, and prefer the **latest stable** APIs/patterns.
- Don’t hand-roll UI primitives (buttons, inputs, modals, tables) if Ant Design provides them.
- Keep Ant Design theming consistent; prefer tokens/theme config over one-off overrides.

## Custom CSS

- If custom styling is needed, use **SCSS Modules** (`*.module.scss`) instead of global CSS.
- Keep styles colocated with the component and name classes by intent (not by appearance).

Example:

```tsx
import { Button } from "antd";
import styles from "./TradeForm.module.scss";

export function TradeFormSubmit() {
  return (
    <Button type="primary" className={styles.submit}>
      Submit
    </Button>
  );
}
```
